The test plan and testing discussions were used to verify that implemented features matched the original functional requirements. My role involved reviewing features from a user perspective and identifying usability issues during testing.
For example, transport information features were reviewed to ensure timetable updates displayed clearly and users could access important information quickly. I also identified situations where excessive information on a single page reduced usability for first-time users.
Testing helped the team identify problems early and improve the overall user experience before final submission
